---
/**
 * Backstage Science page – Updated July 15, 2025
 * – Bold jump‑to buttons with site palette
 * – Smooth scroll + anchor links
 * – Video max‑height and 9/16 aspect‑ratio kept
 * - Text justified with last line centered
 */
export const title = "Backstage Science";

const videos = {
  colinDave: {
    title: "Colin & Dave – Linkin Park (Hellfest 2025)",
    src: "https://thebigbangcollective.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/Linkin+Park+x+Hellfest+2025.mp4",
  },
  jimDigby: {
    title: "Jim Digby – Linkin Park Tour Director (Hellfest 2025)",
    src: "https://thebigbangcollective.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/Jim+Digby+x+Hellfest+2025.mp4",
  },
  jordanRudess: {
    title: "Jordan Rudess – Dream Theater (Hellfest 2025)",
    src: "https://thebigbangcollective.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/Dream+Theater+-+Hellfest+2025.mp4",
  },
  neilWestfall: {
    title: "Neil Westfall – A Day To Remember (Hellfest 2025)",
    src: "https://thebigbangcollective.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/ADTR_HellFest+2025.mp4",
  },
  micahNelson: {
    title: "Micah Nelson – Particle Kid (Montreux Jazz 2025)",
    src: "https://thebigbangcollective.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/Micah+Nelson+x+Montreux+Jazz+Festival+2025.mp4",
  },
};
const currentPath = (Astro.url.pathname.replace(/\/$/, "") || "/");
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>{title} | The Big Bang Collective</title>
    <style>
      /* smooth anchor scrolling */
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,
          "Segoe UI", Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, "Open Sans",
          "Helvetica Neue", sans-serif;
        background: #fff;
      }

      .backstage-science {
        color: #1a1a1a;
        max-width: 75ch;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;
      }

      h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; text-align: center; padding-bottom: 30px;}
      h2 {
        font-size: 1.8rem;
        margin: 3rem 0 1rem;
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #e0e0e0;
      }
      p {
        line-height: 1.6;
        text-align: justify;
        text-align-last: center;
      }

      /* intro panel */
      .intro-panel {
        background: #f5f5f5;
        border-left: 4px solid #ccc;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
      }

      /* jump menu & buttons */
      .festival-nav {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 0.75rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }
      .jump-btn {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
        border-radius: 0.375rem;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 500;
        color: #fff;
        transition: opacity 0.2s;
      }
      .jump-btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; }

      /* your site’s bold colours */
      .jump-btn.hellfest    { background-color: #681717; }
      .jump-btn.montreux    { background-color: #134372; }

      /* video blocks */
      .video-block {
        margin: 2rem 0 3rem;
      }
      .video-block figure {
        margin: 1rem auto 0;
        max-width: 420px;
      }
      .video-block video {
        max-width: 100%;
        margin: auto;
        height: auto;
        max-height: 400px;
        aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
        border-radius: 0.5rem;
        background: #000;
        object-fit: cover;
        display: block;
      }
      .video-block figcaption {
        margin-top: 0.5rem;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        text-align: center;
        color: #333;
      }
      .video-block:target { scroll-margin-top: 2rem; }
      
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <section class="backstage-science">
        <h1>{title}</h1>

        <nav class="festival-nav">
          <a href="#linkin-park-colin-dave" class="jump-btn hellfest">
            Hellfest ’25: Colin &amp; Dave
          </a>
          <a href="#jim-digby" class="jump-btn hellfest">
            Hellfest: Jim Digby
          </a>
          <a href="#jordan-rudess" class="jump-btn hellfest">
            Hellfest: Jordan Rudess
          </a>
          <a href="#neil-westfall" class="jump-btn hellfest">
            Hellfest: Neil Westfall
          </a>
          <a href="#micah-nelson" class="jump-btn montreux">
            Montreux Jazz ’25
          </a>
        </nav>

        <div class="intro-panel">
          <p>
            The Big Bang Collective have been meeting up with members of some of
            the coolest bands around at Festivals this Summer, talking
            backstage with musicians about their interest in science and
            technology, where are we going with A.I. and all things creative
            and emotional. This coming together of people from the science and
            artistic world in an informal, relaxed environment, continues to
            show how closely science and art are intertwined, right down to
            the long, stressful, tiring process of producing an album or a
            science experiment. The similarities are there, but rarely seen
            because they are often hidden from public view. But the creative
            and intellectual challenges are strikingly similar.
          </p>
          <p><strong>We are calling this Backstage Science.</strong></p>
          <p>
            First is a series of chats that Big Bang Collective member Eduardo
            Saenz de Cabezón had backstage at Hellfest 2025.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="linkin-park-colin-dave">HELLFEST 2025</h2>
        <div class="video-block">
          <p>
            His first connection was with Colin and Dave from Linkin Park, how
            they see using A.I. in music and the creative process, take a look:
          </p>
          <figure>
            <video
              controls
              src={`${videos.colinDave.src}#t=0.1`}
              title={videos.colinDave.title}
              preload="metadata"
            />
            <figcaption>{videos.colinDave.title}</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class="video-block" id="jim-digby">
          <p>
            Jim Digby, Linkin Park’s long time, highly respected Tour
            Director, made time for a chat with Eduardo too backstage, giving
            us some insights into how science has changed the way he carries
            out key tasks in the tour management process:
          </p>
          <figure>
            <video
              controls
              src={`${videos.jimDigby.src}#t=0.1`}
              title={videos.jimDigby.title}
              preload="metadata"
            />
            <figcaption>{videos.jimDigby.title}</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class="video-block" id="jordan-rudess">
          <p>
            Eduardo went on to have a great chat with Jordan Rudess from Dream
            Theater, who is already working on a project with a team at
            M.I.T. in Boston using A.I. Hear the full chat:
          </p>
          <figure>
            <video
              controls
              src={`${videos.jordanRudess.src}#t=0.1`}
              title={videos.jordanRudess.title}
              preload="metadata"
            />
            <figcaption>{videos.jordanRudess.title}</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class="video-block" id="neil-westfall">
          <p>
            And the final dressing room that Eduardo invaded was that of the
            very cool Neil Westfall of ADTR. Big Bang Collective member Connie
            Potter welcomed him and the rest of the band for a CERN tour, and
            Neil shares his reaction to being at this unique, world famous
            science facility as well as what he thought of science at school:
          </p>
          <figure>
            <video
              controls
              src={`${videos.neilWestfall.src}#t=0.1`}
              title={videos.neilWestfall.title}
              preload="metadata"
            />
            <figcaption>{videos.neilWestfall.title}</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <h2 id="micah-nelson">MONTREUX JAZZ FESTIVAL 2025</h2>
        <div class="video-block">
          <p>
            At the Montreux Jazz Festival, Big Bang Collective member Connie
            Potter spent a few hours backstage at the Neil Young show, chatting
            with the team and specifically with Micah Nelson, guitarist with
            the Chrome Hearts. Neil also goes by the name Particle Kid and his
            fascination with science is clear to see. He even told us about a
            show he did a few years back incorporating an extraordinary natural
            process called cymatics. It blew our mind, and we have a feeling
            we’ll be hearing more from Micah in the future. Watch our chat
            with Micah Nelson here:
          </p>
          <figure>
            <video
              controls
              src={`${videos.micahNelson.src}#t=0.1`}
              title={videos.micahNelson.title}
              preload="metadata"
            />
            <figcaption>{videos.micahNelson.title}</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>